{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b4f099a9-0182-47ad-aca1-dad135219446","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"932ce619-82a3-487b-8ac1-ace155d18b44","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"BD08:2F6EDC:1E8E15D:223BC64:6A07C4BD"},"id":"cb7daffd-03fd-4d32-b858-a78be8dde030","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:40.126Z","parentId":"94ea1b45-37f0-4c04-a94c-cfd77eb7c923"}
